    <briefdescription>
<para>The UID (caller + entry IDs) of an ITS entry. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This is a packed, 32-bit version of <computeroutput>psa_storage_uid_t</computeroutput> which allows storing smaller IDs compared to the 64-bit ones that PSA Secure Storage specifies. Zephyr defines ranges of IDs to be used by different users of the API (subsystems, application) which guarantees 1. no collisions and 2. that the IDs used fit within <computeroutput>uid</computeroutput>. <simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="key__ids_8h" kindref="compound">zephyr/psa/key_ids.h</ref> and the other header files under <computeroutput>zephyr/psa</computeroutput>. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
